								StaticText '\ue605\ue605\ue605\ue605\ue605'
								StaticText '\ue605\ue605\ue605\ue605\ue605'
								StaticText '100%'
						StaticText 'Arrived properly factory packaged in a 5-pack zip top "baggie." First one out of the bag worked perfectly. Loaded lots of music onto it for my car. No problems, good manufacturer, good price for the 5-pack.'

						StaticText 'Great and reliable value for USB 2.0 Thumbdrives.'
						[1887] LayoutTable ''

									StaticText 'Rating'
								StaticText '\ue605\ue605\ue605\ue605\ue605'
								StaticText '\ue605\ue605\ue605\ue605\ue605'
								StaticText '100%'
						StaticText 'Bought these for an IT software deployment project at work. They were exactly what I needed. They are NOT USB 3.0 so if you want transfer speed, get the USB 3.0 version. But for decent drives at a good price, you really can\'t go wrong here. I used them for an entire week deploying software to over a hundred laptops and none of them failed in any way. I\'ve learned in my career never to buy the really cheap no name drives. I thought the "Everything But Stromboli" lanyard was funny too.'

						StaticText 'These work well for storing photos, documents, etc.This would have received 5 stars, one for each USB drive, had it not been for one of the packages cut open on the connecting end.If you receive one of these cut open, do not use it because it may have been tampered with. Contact Amazon about it and they will fix the problem.'

								StaticText '100%'
						StaticText 'I bought these to serve as backups for a new batch of laptops.=== The Good Stuff ===* They worked well for creating Windows10 system backup disks.* All five worked OK. They loaded the first time, and I checked them after a couple days, and all the data was intact.* The sliding plastic case seemed a little too cute, but worked fine.=== The Not-So-Good Stuff ===* Two lanyards? C\'mon, these things must have cost about a half a cent each, you couldn\'t throw three more in the box?=== Summary ===I only used these for one very specific use, and they have worked well. No idea how long they will last in "daily" use.'

								StaticText '40%'
						StaticText 'I have been buying San Disk USB memory in the past years without problem. This time, I wanted smaller capacity memory. 5 USB memory with 32GM were perfect.However, after the product arrived, I began to have the bad experience. One of them automatically turned its own write protection on. I talked with Amazon customer service and got refund for this one USB memory. One month later, 2nd USB memory rejected to write the data because of write protection. Then, 3rd USB memory showed only 9GM capacity available even though I copied the files with 7GB capacity. When I deleted the files in order to increase the capacity, the memory capacity was not changed at all. 3 out of 5 USB memory were useless.I gave up on those 32GB USB memory and ordered a larger one, 128GB, made by SanDisk. This 128GB does not show any write protection behavior at all.'

step_data.thought:
I'm currently on the product page for the SanDisk Cruzer Glide 32GB USB flash drive, and I can see I'm in the reviews section as indicated by the URL ending with '#reviews' and the 'Reviews (12)' tab being expanded and selected.

Looking at the information on the page, I can see the following rating details:
- Overall rating: 70% of 100
- Total number of reviews: 12

The reviews are displayed in a list format. I can see individual reviews with:
- Review titles
- Individual ratings (shown as percentages)
- Review content
- Reviewer names
- Dates posted

Specifically, I can see reviews such as:
1. "Excellent value" - 100% rating by bykboi
2. "Great and reliable value for USB 2.0 Thumbdrives" - 100% rating by Chad T
3. "Great Product If Unopened" - 80% rating by JW
